The Brazil international became an instant fan favourite at Goodison Park after making an initial £35 million switch from Watford in summer 2018. He also played an integral role in Frank Lampard’s side avoiding Premier League relegation last season by scoring six goals in their final nine games. But Richarlison opened up the prospect of leaving the Blues this summer by admitting on Monday that he has held discussions with the club’s hierarchy. -Advertisement- “I’ve already made it clear to the board,” he told Globo Esporte. “I’ve already talked to Lampard too, with my managers and they know what I want. Let’s wait for June. “Now I can’t talk, because when I talk about leaving a club I’m kind of like this, because of the history I have at Everton, the affection that the fans have for me. “When I talk about leaving, I’m kind of speechless.”